**Analysis of the Target Image**

1. **Overall Count and Layers**

   - **Total Blocks:** 18  
   - **Left Group (5 blocks)**  
     • Bottom layer: 3 red arches.  
     • Above the center arch: 1 green rectangular block.  
     • On top of that green block: 1 red arch.  
   - **Right Group (13 blocks)**  
     • Bottom/front layer: 2 red arches.  
     • Second/front layer: 1 blue cube, 1 orange rectangular block, plus 2 yellow half‐cylinders side by side.  
     • Third/front layer (roofs): 2 orange triangular “roof” blocks.  
     • Rear vertical layer: 2 tall yellow rectangular blocks and 1 tall green block in between.  
     • Rear roof layer: 2 more orange “roof” blocks (one on each yellow pillar).  

2. **Which Dictionary Blocks Are Used (and How Often)**

   - Red arch (index 1) → 6 times  
   - Blue cube (index 2) → 1 time  
   - Green horizontal rectangular block (index 5) → 1 time  
   - Tall green rectangular block (index 6) → 1 time  
   - Tall yellow rectangular block (index 9) → 2 times  
   - Yellow half‐cylinder (index 11) → 2 times  
   - Orange rectangular block (index 13) → 1 time  
   - Orange roof block (index 15) → 4 times  

   (Note that the same block‐index may be reused multiple times, exactly in the orientation shown in the dictionary.)

**Step‐by‐Step Assembly Instructions**

Use the following notation:  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index X  
  Step2: Move block with index Y  
  …  
}

Below is one possible build order (bottom‐to‐top, left‐to‐right):

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 1   // Leftmost red arch (left group base)
  Step2:  Move block with index 1   // Middle red arch (left group base)
  Step3:  Move block with index 1   // Right red arch (left group base)
  Step4:  Move block with index 5   // Green rectangle on top of middle arch
  Step5:  Move block with index 1   // Red arch on top of green rectangle

  Step6:  Move block with index 1   // Bottom left arch (right group)
  Step7:  Move block with index 1   // Bottom right arch (right group)
  Step8:  Move block with index 2   // Blue cube atop left arch
  Step9:  Move block with index 13  // Orange rectangular block atop right arch
  Step10: Move block with index 11  // First yellow half‐cylinder (front)
  Step11: Move block with index 11  // Second yellow half‐cylinder (front)
  Step12: Move block with index 15  // Orange roof on blue cube
  Step13: Move block with index 15  // Orange roof on orange rectangular block

  Step14: Move block with index 9   // Tall yellow block (left rear)
  Step15: Move block with index 6   // Tall green block (middle rear)
  Step16: Move block with index 9   // Tall yellow block (right rear)
  Step17: Move block with index 15  // Orange roof on left yellow pillar
  Step18: Move block with index 15  // Orange roof on right yellow pillar
}
